        "date_of_stay": "01-08-2023",
        "review": "We stayed at Tui Blu Bahari Zanzibar in August 2023, for a 10-night stay. There were 4 adults and 2 children (aged 9 and 7). We were greeted in reception with a lovely Hibiscus cold drink and Celestin did a great job of explaining the resort and helping us download the app to our phones. There is a fridge with cold drinks and snacks that you can access throughout the day and evening in reception.  We had two rooms and our room was spacious for the 4 of us, with a large bed and a sofa bed already made up for the kids to sleep in. Both had mosquito nets in place. We had a lovely garden patio with a table and chairs and also an egg chair. We were in a ground-floor room with a limited partial view of the sea, due to the trees and plants surrounding the property, but that was fine for us. The room was clean and furnished well, with plenty of storage.  The grounds are simply beautiful, with plenty of fruit and vegetable trees. The staff work hard to keep the grounds clean and tidy. The hotel is spread out on quite a large area and in the mornings you often see people walking or running along the paths. There is also a fish pond and mini waterfall in the gardens. To get to the beach, pool and restaurants you head down the steps and there are ramps on the side for step free access. When you\u2019re at the bottom of the stairs you will find a TV room, reading room and two shops as well as the pool, bars, restaurants and the beach.  The pool was 1.4m with adjacent splash pool for the little ones. The pool was clean and the water was a lovely temperature. It never felt overcrowded or busy and there were plenty of sunbeds too. The bar at the pool served drinks all day and cakes/biscuits were also available in the afternoon. The staff often came round during the day to the sunbeds taking drink orders with a smile. The beach area is private to the hotel and also had plenty of sunbeds and a bar. There was a lovely breeze here, so if the weather gets a bit too much, then consider sitting on the beach area. The tide was out most mornings and came back in mid-afternoon. The water was lovely and warm. The main beach is public and there are a lot of local sellers on the beach selling their wares, as well as taking trips to see starfish \u2013 if you\u2019re not interested, just say so and they will leave you alone. The beach is a bit rocky, so if you do decide to go out, I would take suitable footwear.  The Restaurant is where you can have breakfast, lunch and dinner all buffet with plenty of options. Breakfast was a internationals affair with continental as well as cooked and traditional African dishes. There also plenty of fresh fruits, nuts, yoghurts available. They even served Indian chai! For dinner again there were plenty of choices \u2013 hot and cold, with a pasta station, noodle station and a fish station. There are plenty of different salads, which were so fresh and delicious. There was a vast dessert section again with fresh fruits, but you have to try and the Zanzibar spice ice cream \u2013 it\u2019s delicious. For lunch we used to head to the Green and Grill where you\u2019ll find pizza\u2019s chips, burgers and salads. There are lot of drinks that are included in the all-inclusive price, but some are priced, so check the menus. On Tuesday\u2019s dinner is served by the pool with a live band and on Saturday\u2019s it was served on the beach with a traditional massi performance.  I need to give a HUGE special mention to Chef Yussef and Chef Kabaka who made special veggie Indian meals for my mother-in-law. Everyday they would bring bowls of delicious food just for us and it was so appreciated.  We also dined at The Andiamo Pizzeria which did need to be booked in advance. It was Italian food and was also delicious.  There are lots of activites happening in the evenings and the staff always make them special. On Friday we watched a movie on the beach and other nights there were dance or acrobatics shows. We even did leaf weaving during our stay. There is a gym onsite and also a daily programme of activities. There is a kids play area, but we didn't go, but did look like it was for very young kids.  Overall this hotel is amazing!! The quality of food is exceptional and every day the staff are on hand with a huge smile on their face to make your day a bright and relaxing one. I need to say a special thank you to Fatima and Rebeca who took care of us everyday. Ally and Celestin were great hosts and always were checking on how our stay was going.  If you\u2019re thinking of booking this hotel, just do it, you will not regret it. I hope you return one day!",
