        "date_of_stay": "01-08-2023",
        "review": "Finally found a 10/10 resort Absolutely breathtaking! The wife and I just returned from the most amazing week at this outstanding resort...Tui Blue Bahari was all kinds of perfect for everyone's needs.  Ride from the airport is around 55 minutes, give or take. Resort has the most amazing reef and the tide phenomenon unique to the area. Water in August was still warm 25\u00b0 and great in the afternoons. The resort offers so much for couples wanting that romantic getaway and families looking for that special bonding trip, and yet both groups could holiday with ample space without anyone being in the others space.  We stayed in a Junior Suite which was spacious, comfortable and beautifully designed.  Won't spoil any of the offerings from the signature restaurants but I can say we tried all and theres something for everyone....and yes it's all good.....the baking/bread/dessert dept are very strong.....tried and tested recipes and tasty desserts each day....  Would definitely recommend all inclusive, its well worth it, given the range of restaurants and bars on the resort.  We have never had the resort GM take the time to host an introduction to wine tasting, we have to thank Javier for taking the time to explain and educate us so well, palate felt alot smarter after attending it. You can see the staff respect him and he genuinely interacts with his clients and goes out of his way to help and ensure his guests are taken care of.  There was evening entertainment each night and while it may not be have been Broadway or Cirq du Solei, we appreciated and enjoyed the Proudly Local performances and each were a treat to watch giving you a taste of the unique culture.  The TUI APP is key...alot going on around the resort and alot of activities to book so best get acquainted asap , it was easy enough and we got dinner bookings each night no problem and attended the wonderful reef walk with Julius and ever entertaining Cha cha.  There's even an in-house tour guide and tours/excursion team situated in the rec area and boat house respectively, pricing was very competitive, and they cared more abt safety re water conditions , tides and weather as well as swimming competency for snorkeling etc. You could see they cared abt the guest and offered proper advice vs trying to promote a sale.  We celebrated an Anniversary and I think we only mentioned it once, when we called to confirm booking abt 2 days before arrival, someone remembered and got chef to bake a Happy Anniversary cake, thoughtful gesture and it tasted amazing.  There were so many brilliant personalities we met at the resort that there's too many to mention....but here's a Small shoutout..... Omary is a cocktail wizard at the beach bar.....Zena ..Zelda...Helena ...Gati from Green and Grill always offering great service with a smile and a chat.....Sharifa from housekeeping...omg this lady is a towel genuis....different creation each day! Manager mathew from Green and Grill...Mo aziz + Ally...Hussein and Leah from Reception....The client service is exceptional and everyone went out of their way to make our trip special and memorable. The staff really are exceptional and have made our experience.  This resort was so outstanding we have started searching other Tui blues to see where we could go next:)  You can see from introduction handshake to service delivery and goodbyes its all about the client and making sure they had a positive experience. Will definitely be back, we left out some tours on purpose to go back with family. Its been a week and we have withdrawal symptoms:) Well done to Javier and the Tui Blue team in Zanzibar....you all gave us a great holiday!",
