        "review": "Amazing hotel after a week on safari.  Personal service from the staff who remember your fav drink, what you like for breakfast, where you like to sit in the restaurant.  Room was large with a spacious bedroom, large bathroom. Beds had mosquito nets. Rooms were sprayed every night and nets closed.  Plenty of choice of food at the restaurants, different dishes each night, plenty of snacks and drinks available during the day. Full bar menu of drinks - plenty of mocktails for the non-drinker. Some of the high end drinks are pay for even on All Inclusive.  Hotel right on the beach, at low tide the sea in quite fair out which allows for beach walks (starfish and crabs can be seen).  Hotel grounds are well kept and cared for.  Hotel is about an hour drive from Stone Town and the Airport, taxi will cost around $40 each way. Stone Town is worth a day visit, can easily find a guide when you get there if you get dropped at the Fort, online guides cost $30 per person, we paid $30 for 4 person for 2/3 hour walking tour. Prison Island worth a visit, again head to the seafront and you will find private boat owners willing to do the crossing for a lot less than booking online (just check condition of the boat - online we were quoted $100, did crossing for $35).  In the shops around Stone Town, haggle hard - it's part of the fun of shopping.  All in all a great way to spend a weeks holiday.",
